==English==

===Etymology===
From {{ME.}} ''[[chois]]'' < {{OF.}} ''[[choisir]]'' "to choose".

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-choice.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪs|-ɔɪs]]

===Noun===
'''choice'''
# An [[option]]; a [[decision]]; an opportunity to [[choose]] or [[select]] something.
#:''Do I have a '''choice''' of what color to paint it?''
# One [[selection]] or [[preference]]; that which is chosen or decided; the [[outcome]] of a [[decision]].
#:''The ice cream sundae is a popular '''choice''' for dessert.''
# Anything that can be choosen.
# (''definite'': '''the choice'''): The best or most preferable part

====Synonyms====
*(''anything that can be choosen''): [[assortment]], [[range]], [[selection]]
*(''definite: best or most preferable part''): the [[cream]]

